The paper focuses on benchmarking and characterizing Deep Neural Networks on embedded platforms, specifically for image processing tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the integration of ARM's Streamline Performance Analyser and the development of a multi-variable linear regression model, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-categories of Computer Architecture (cs.AR) and Embedded Systems (cs.EM). Finally, the paper addresses the need for energy-efficient solutions, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
